wlsxNGBICInserted.description: A Trap which indicates that a GBIC is inserted in a Line Card.

wlsxNProcessDied.name: wlsxNProcessDied
wlsxNProcessDied.description: A Trap which indicates that a process has died.

wlsxNProcessExceedsMemoryLimits.name: wlsxNProcessExceedsMemoryLimits
wlsxNProcessExceedsMemoryLimits.description: A Trap which indicates that a process is consuming Large amounts of memory.

wlsxNLowOnFlashSpace.name: wlsxNLowOnFlashSpace
wlsxNLowOnFlashSpace.description: A Trap which indicates that the controller is running low on flash space.

wlsxNLowMemory.name: wlsxNLowMemory
wlsxNLowMemory.description: A Trap which indicates that the system free memory is low.

wlsxNFanTrayRemoved.name: wlsxNFanTrayRemoved
wlsxNFanTrayRemoved.description: A Trap which indicates that a fan tray is removed.

wlsxNFanTrayInserted.name: wlsxNFanTrayInserted
wlsxNFanTrayInserted.description: A Trap which indicates that a fan tray is inserted.

wlsxNLCRemoved.name: wlsxNLCRemoved
wlsxNLCRemoved.description: A Trap which indicates that a Line card is removed.

wlsxNPowerSupplyMissing.name: wlsxNPowerSupplyMissing
wlsxNPowerSupplyMissing.description: A Trap which indicates that the power supply is missing.

wlsxNAccessPointIsUp.name: wlsxNAccessPointIsUp
wlsxNAccessPointIsUp.description: A Trap which indicates that an access point up.

wlsxNAccessPointIsDown.name: wlsxNAccessPointIsDown
wlsxNAccessPointIsDown.description: A Trap which indicates that an access point down.

wlsxNCoverageHoleDetected.name: wlsxNCoverageHoleDetected
wlsxNCoverageHoleDetected.description: This trap indicates that an access point at Location wlsxTrapAPLocation has detected a Coverage Hole.

wlsxNChannelChanged.name: wlsxNChannelChanged
wlsxNChannelChanged.description: This trap indicates that an access point at Location wlsxTrapAPLocation has changed the channel.

wlsxNStationAddedToBlackList.name: wlsxNStationAddedToBlackList
wlsxNStationAddedToBlackList.description: This trap indicates that the station is black listed.

wlsxNStationRemovedFromBlackList.name: wlsxNStationRemovedFromBlackList
wlsxNStationRemovedFromBlackList.description: This trap indicates that the station is removed from the black list.

wlsxNIpSpoofingDetected.name: wlsxNIpSpoofingDetected
wlsxNIpSpoofingDetected.description: A trap indicating that the controller detected IP Spoofing.

wlsxNDBCommunicationFailure.name: wlsxNDBCommunicationFailure
wlsxNDBCommunicationFailure.description: This trap indicates that communication with Database failed.

wlsxNVrrpStateChange.name: wlsxNVrrpStateChange
wlsxNVrrpStateChange.description: This trap indicates that VRRP state has changed on the controller.

wlsxNRadioAttributesChanged.name: wlsxNRadioAttributesChanged
wlsxNRadioAttributesChanged.description: A Trap which indicates changes in the Radio attributes of an access point.

wlsxNESIServerUp.name: wlsxNESIServerUp
wlsxNESIServerUp.description: A Trap which indicates that a ESI server is up.

wlsxNESIServerDown.name: wlsxNESIServerDown
wlsxNESIServerDown.description: A Trap which indicates that a ESI server is down.

wlsxNLicenseExpiry.name: wlsxNLicenseExpiry
wlsxNLicenseExpiry.description: A Trap which indicates that one or more licenses on the controller will expire in wlsxTrapLicenseDaysRemaining days.

wlsxUnsecureAPDetected.name: wlsxUnsecureAPDetected
wlsxUnsecureAPDetected.description: This trap indicates that an unauthorized access point is connected to the wired network. The access point is declared Rogue because it was matched to a MAC address.

wlsxUnsecureAPResolved.name: wlsxUnsecureAPResolved
wlsxUnsecureAPResolved.description: This trap indicates that a previously detected access point, classified as Rogue, is no longer present in the network.

wlsxStaImpersonation.name: wlsxStaImpersonation
wlsxStaImpersonation.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected Station Impersonation.

wlsxReservedChannelViolation.name: wlsxReservedChannelViolation
wlsxReservedChannelViolation.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected an access point which is violating the Reserved Channel configuration.

wlsxValidSSIDViolation.name: wlsxValidSSIDViolation
wlsxValidSSIDViolation.description: This trap indicates that an AP has detected an access point is violating Valid SSID configuration by using an SSID that is reserved for use by a valid AP only.

wlsxChannelMisconfiguration.name: wlsxChannelMisconfiguration
wlsxChannelMisconfiguration.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an access point that has a channel misconfiguration because it is using a channel that is not valid.

wlsxOUIMisconfiguration.name: wlsxOUIMisconfiguration
wlsxOUIMisconfiguration.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an access point that has an OUI misconfiguration because it is using an OUI that is not valid.

wlsxSSIDMisconfiguration.name: wlsxSSIDMisconfiguration
wlsxSSIDMisconfiguration.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an access point that has an SSID misconfiguration because it is using an SSID that is not valid.

wlsxShortPreableMisconfiguration.name: wlsxShortPreableMisconfiguration
wlsxShortPreableMisconfiguration.description: This trap indicates that an access point has bad Short preamble configuration.

wlsxWPAMisconfiguration.name: wlsxWPAMisconfiguration
wlsxWPAMisconfiguration.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an access point that is misconfigured because it is not using WPA.

wlsxAdhocNetworkDetected.name: wlsxAdhocNetworkDetected
wlsxAdhocNetworkDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AM has detected an Ad hoc network.

wlsxAdhocNetworkRemoved.name: wlsxAdhocNetworkRemoved
wlsxAdhocNetworkRemoved.description: This trap indicates that a previously detected Ad hoc Network is no longer present in the network.

wlsxStaPolicyViolation.name: wlsxStaPolicyViolation
wlsxStaPolicyViolation.description: This trap indicates that Protection was enforced because a valid station's association to a non-valid access point violated Valid Station policy. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0008 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019

wlsxRepeatWEPIVViolation.name: wlsxRepeatWEPIVViolation
wlsxRepeatWEPIVViolation.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a valid access point is using the same WEP initialization vector in consecutive packets.

wlsxWeakWEPIVViolation.name: wlsxWeakWEPIVViolation
wlsxWeakWEPIVViolation.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a valid access point is using a Weak WEP initialization vector. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0021

wlsxChannelInterferenceDetected.name: wlsxChannelInterferenceDetected
wlsxChannelInterferenceDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP has detected channel interference.

wlsxChannelInterferenceCleared.name: wlsxChannelInterferenceCleared
wlsxChannelInterferenceCleared.description: This trap indicates that a previously detected channel interference is no longer present.

wlsxAPInterferenceDetected.name: wlsxAPInterferenceDetected
wlsxAPInterferenceDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP has detected interference for an access point.

wlsxAPInterferenceCleared.name: wlsxAPInterferenceCleared
wlsxAPInterferenceCleared.description: This trap indicates that the previously detected interference for an access point is no longer present.

wlsxStaInterferenceDetected.name: wlsxStaInterferenceDetected
wlsxStaInterferenceDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP has detected interference for a station.

wlsxStaInterferenceCleared.name: wlsxStaInterferenceCleared
wlsxStaInterferenceCleared.description: This trap indicates that the previously detected interference for a station is no longer present.

wlsxFrameRetryRateExceeded.name: wlsxFrameRetryRateExceeded
wlsxFrameRetryRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that an access point has exceeded the configured upper threshold for Frame Retry Rate.

wlsxFrameReceiveErrorRateExceeded.name: wlsxFrameReceiveErrorRateExceeded
wlsxFrameReceiveErrorRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that an access point has exceeded the configured upper threshold for Frame Receive Error Rate.

wlsxFrameFragmentationRateExceeded.name: wlsxFrameFragmentationRateExceeded
wlsxFrameFragmentationRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that an access point exceeded the configured upper threshold for Frame Fragmentation Rate.

wlsxFrameBandWidthRateExceeded.name: wlsxFrameBandWidthRateExceeded
wlsxFrameBandWidthRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a station or access point has exceeded the configured upper threshold for Bandwidth rate.

wlsxFrameLowSpeedRateExceeded.name: wlsxFrameLowSpeedRateExceeded
wlsxFrameLowSpeedRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a station has exceeded the configured upper threshold for Low speed rate.

wlsxFrameNonUnicastRateExceeded.name: wlsxFrameNonUnicastRateExceeded
wlsxFrameNonUnicastRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a station has exceeded the configured upper threshold for Non Unicast traffic rate.

wlsxLoadbalancingEnabled.name: wlsxLoadbalancingEnabled
wlsxLoadbalancingEnabled.description: This trap indicates that an AM is reporting that an AP has enabled Load balancing.

wlsxLoadbalancingDisabled.name: wlsxLoadbalancingDisabled
wlsxLoadbalancingDisabled.description: This trap indicates that an AM is reporting that an AP has enabled Load balancing.

wlsxChannelFrameRetryRateExceeded.name: wlsxChannelFrameRetryRateExceeded
wlsxChannelFrameRetryRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP has detected that the configured upper threshold for Frame Retry Rate was exceeded on a channel.

wlsxChannelFrameFragmentationRateExceede.name: wlsxChannelFrameFragmentationRateExceeded
wlsxChannelFrameFragmentationRateExceede.description: This trap indicates that an AP has detected that the configured upper threshold for Frame Fragmentation Rate was exceeded on a channel.

wlsxChannelFrameErrorRateExceeded.name: wlsxChannelFrameErrorRateExceeded
wlsxChannelFrameErrorRateExceeded.description: This trap indicates that an AP has detected that the configured upper threshold for Frame Receive Error Rate was exceeded on a channel.

wlsxSignatureMatchAP.name: wlsxSignatureMatchAP
wlsxSignatureMatchAP.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match in a frame from an access point.

wlsxSignatureMatchSta.name: wlsxSignatureMatchSta
wlsxSignatureMatchSta.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match in a frame from a Station.

wlsxChannelRateAnomaly.name: wlsxChannelRateAnomaly
wlsxChannelRateAnomaly.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected frames on a channel which exceed the configured IDS rate threshold. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0052 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0047 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxNodeRateAnomalyAP.name: wlsxNodeRateAnomalyAP
wlsxNodeRateAnomalyAP.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected frames transmitted or received by an access point, which exceed the configured IDS rate threshold. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0052 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0047 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxNodeRateAnomalySta.name: wlsxNodeRateAnomalySta
wlsxNodeRateAnomalySta.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected frames transmitted or received by a node, which exceed the configured IDS rate threshold.

wlsxEAPRateAnomaly.name: wlsxEAPRateAnomaly
wlsxEAPRateAnomaly.description: This trap indicates that the rate of EAP Handshake packets received by an AP has exceeded the configured IDS EAP Handshake rate threshold. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0049

wlsxSignalAnomaly.name: wlsxSignalAnomaly
wlsxSignalAnomaly.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected a Signal Anomaly.

wlsxSequenceNumberAnomalyAP.name: wlsxSequenceNumberAnomalyAP
wlsxSequenceNumberAnomalyAP.description: This trap indicates that an AM received packets from an AP which exceeds the acceptable sequence number difference. The acceptable sequence number difference is an IDS configuration object. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0061 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0008 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0047 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxSequenceNumberAnomalySta.name: wlsxSequenceNumberAnomalySta
wlsxSequenceNumberAnomalySta.description: This trap indicates that an AM received packets from a Node which exceeds the acceptable sequence number difference. The acceptable sequence number difference is an IDS configuration object. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0061 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0008 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0047 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxDisconnectStationAttack.name: wlsxDisconnectStationAttack
wlsxDisconnectStationAttack.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected a station Disconnect attack. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxApFloodAttack.name: wlsxApFloodAttack
wlsxApFloodAttack.description: This trap indicates that the number of potential fake APs detected by an AP has exceeded the configured IDS threshold. This is the total number of fake APs observed across all bands. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0056

wlsxAdhocNetwork.name: wlsxAdhocNetwork
wlsxAdhocNetwork.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected an Ad hoc Network. An Station is connected to an ad hoc AP.

wlsxWirelessBridge.name: wlsxWirelessBridge
wlsxWirelessBridge.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a Wireless Bridge when a WDS frame was seen between the transmitter and receiver addresses.

wlsxInvalidMacOUIAP.name: wlsxInvalidMacOUIAP
wlsxInvalidMacOUIAP.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an invalid MAC OUI in the BSSID of a frame. An invalid MAC OUI suggests that the frame may be spoofed.

wlsxInvalidMacOUISta.name: wlsxInvalidMacOUISta
wlsxInvalidMacOUISta.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an invalid MAC OUI in the SRC or DST address of a frame. An invalid MAC OUI suggests that the frame may be spoofed.

wlsxWEPMisconfiguration.name: wlsxWEPMisconfiguration
wlsxWEPMisconfiguration.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an access point that is misconfigured because it does not have Privacy enabled.

wlsxStaRepeatWEPIVViolation.name: wlsxStaRepeatWEPIVViolation
wlsxStaRepeatWEPIVViolation.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a valid station is using the same WEP initialization vector in consecutive packets.

wlsxStaWeakWEPIVViolation.name: wlsxStaWeakWEPIVViolation
wlsxStaWeakWEPIVViolation.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a valid station is using a Weak WEP initialization vector.

wlsxStaAssociatedToUnsecureAP.name: wlsxStaAssociatedToUnsecureAP
wlsxStaAssociatedToUnsecureAP.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected a client associated with a Rogue access point.

wlsxStaUnAssociatedFromUnsecureAP.name: wlsxStaUnAssociatedFromUnsecureAP
wlsxStaUnAssociatedFromUnsecureAP.description: This trap indicates that a previously detected rogue access point association is no longer present.

wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetected.name: wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetected
wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AM has detected an Ad hoc network that is bridging to a wired network

wlsxInterferingApDetected.name: wlsxInterferingApDetected
wlsxInterferingApDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an access point classified as Interfering. The access point is declared Interfering because it is neither authorized or classified as Rogue.

wlsxPortUp.name: wlsxPortUp
wlsxPortUp.description: This trap indicates that a Physical port is up.

wlsxPortDown.name: wlsxPortDown
wlsxPortDown.description: This trap indicates that a Physical port is Down.

wlsxBSSIDIsUp.name: wlsxBSSIDIsUp
wlsxBSSIDIsUp.description: A Trap which indicates that an access point BSSID is up.

wlsxBSSIDIsDown.name: wlsxBSSIDIsDown
wlsxBSSIDIsDown.description: A Trap which indicates that an access point BSSID is down.

wlsxColdStart.name: wlsxColdStart
wlsxColdStart.description: An enterprise version of cold start trap, which contains the controller time stamp.

wlsxWarmStart.name: wlsxWarmStart
wlsxWarmStart.description: An enterprise version of warm start trap, which contains the controller time stamp.

wlsxAPImpersonation.name: wlsxAPImpersonation
wlsxAPImpersonation.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected AP Impersonation because the number of beacons seen has exceeded the expected number by the configured percentage threshold. The expected number is calculated based on the Beacon Interval Field in the Beacon frame.

wlsxInformQueueOverFlow.name: wlsxInformQueueOverFlow
wlsxInformQueueOverFlow.description: This trap indicates that an Inform queue overflow condition occurred.

wlsxNAuthServerIsDown.name: wlsxNAuthServerIsDown
wlsxNAuthServerIsDown.description: This trap indicates that an authentication server is down.

wlsxCTSTransferError.name: wlsxCTSTransferError
wlsxCTSTransferError.description: This trap indicates the status of the configuration transfer from the management station.

wlsxCTSTransferSucceeded.name: wlsxCTSTransferSucceeded
wlsxCTSTransferSucceeded.description: This trap indicates the status of the configuration transfer from the management station.

wlsxConfigurationUpdateError.name: wlsxConfigurationUpdateError
wlsxConfigurationUpdateError.description: This trap indicates the configuration update status.

wlsxConfigurationUpdateSucceeded.name: wlsxConfigurationUpdateSucceeded
wlsxConfigurationUpdateSucceeded.description: This trap indicates the configuration update status.

wlsxGlobalConfigurationChangeNotificatio.name: wlsxGlobalConfigurationChangeNotification
wlsxGlobalConfigurationChangeNotificatio.description: This trap indicates that global configuration was modified on the controller.

wlsxUserEntryChanged.name: wlsxUserEntryChanged
wlsxUserEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the user configuration has changed.

wlsxAPBssidEntryChanged.name: wlsxAPBssidEntryChanged
wlsxAPBssidEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the BSSID configuration has changed.

wlsxAPRadioEntryChanged.name: wlsxAPRadioEntryChanged
wlsxAPRadioEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the Radio configuration has changed.

wlsxAPEntryChanged.name: wlsxAPEntryChanged
wlsxAPEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the AP configuration has changed.

wlsxSwitchListEntryChanged.name: wlsxSwitchListEntryChanged
wlsxSwitchListEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the controller list has changed.

wlsxPortEntryChanged.name: wlsxPortEntryChanged
wlsxPortEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the port configuration has changed.

wlsxVlanEntryChanged.name: wlsxVlanEntryChanged
wlsxVlanEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the VLAN configuration has changed.

wlsxVlanInterfaceEntryChanged.name: wlsxVlanInterfaceEntryChanged
wlsxVlanInterfaceEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the VLAN Interface configuration has changed.

wlsxWindowsBridgeDetected.name: wlsxWindowsBridgeDetected
wlsxWindowsBridgeDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AM has detected a station that is bridging from a wireless network to a wired network

wlsxLicenseEntryChanged.name: wlsxLicenseEntryChanged
wlsxLicenseEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the license table has changed.

wlsxEsiServerChanged.name: wlsxEsiServerChanged
wlsxEsiServerChanged.description: This trap indicates that the ESI server table has changed.

wlsxMonAPEntryChanged.name: wlsxMonAPEntryChanged
wlsxMonAPEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that a monitored AP entry changed

wlsxMonStationEntryChanged.name: wlsxMonStationEntryChanged
wlsxMonStationEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that a monitored station entry changed

wlsxSignAPNetstumbler.name: wlsxSignAPNetstumbler
wlsxSignAPNetstumbler.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Netstumbler from an access point. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0025

wlsxSignStaNetstumbler.name: wlsxSignStaNetstumbler
wlsxSignStaNetstumbler.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Netstumbler from a Station. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0025

wlsxSignAPAsleap.name: wlsxSignAPAsleap
wlsxSignAPAsleap.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for ASLEAP from an access point. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0027

wlsxSignStaAsleap.name: wlsxSignStaAsleap
wlsxSignStaAsleap.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for ASLEAP from a Station. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0027

wlsxSignAPAirjack.name: wlsxSignAPAirjack
wlsxSignAPAirjack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for AirJack from an access point. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0018

wlsxSignStaAirjack.name: wlsxSignStaAirjack
wlsxSignStaAirjack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for AirJack from a Station. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0018

wlsxSignAPNullProbeResp.name: wlsxSignAPNullProbeResp
wlsxSignAPNullProbeResp.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Null-Probe-Response from an access point. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0064

wlsxSignStaNullProbeResp.name: wlsxSignStaNullProbeResp
wlsxSignStaNullProbeResp.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Null-Probe-Response from a Station. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0064

wlsxSignAPDeauthBcast.name: wlsxSignAPDeauthBcast
wlsxSignAPDeauthBcast.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Deauth-Broadcast from an access point. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045

wlsxSignStaDeauthBcast.name: wlsxSignStaDeauthBcast
wlsxSignStaDeauthBcast.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Deauth-Broadcast from a Station. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045

wlsxWindowsBridgeDetectedAP.name: wlsxWindowsBridgeDetectedAP
wlsxWindowsBridgeDetectedAP.description: This trap indicates that an AP is detecting an access point that is bridging from a wireless network to a wired network.

wlsxWindowsBridgeDetectedSta.name: wlsxWindowsBridgeDetectedSta
wlsxWindowsBridgeDetectedSta.description: This trap indicates that an AP is detecting a station that is bridging from a wireless network to a wired network.

wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedAP.name: wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedAP
wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedAP.description: This trap indicates that an AM has detected an Ad hoc network that is bridging to a wired network

wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedSta.name: wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedSta
wlsxAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedSta.description: This trap indicates that an AM has detected an Ad hoc network that is bridging to a wired network

wlsxDisconnectStationAttackAP.name: wlsxDisconnectStationAttackAP
wlsxDisconnectStationAttackAP.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected a station disconnect attack. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxDisconnectStationAttackSta.name: wlsxDisconnectStationAttackSta
wlsxDisconnectStationAttackSta.description: This trap indicates that an AM detected a station Disconnect attack. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxSuspectUnsecureAPDetected.name: wlsxSuspectUnsecureAPDetected
wlsxSuspectUnsecureAPDetected.description: This trap indicates that an access point, classified as Suspected Rogue, has been detected by a Controller. The AP is suspected to be rogue, with the supplied confidence level, because it was matched to the wired MAC address.

wlsxSuspectUnsecureAPResolved.name: wlsxSuspectUnsecureAPResolved
wlsxSuspectUnsecureAPResolved.description: This trap indicates that a previously detected access point, classified Suspected Rogue, is either no longer present in the network or has changed its state.

wlsxConfigurationLicenseMismatch.name: wlsxConfigurationLicenseMismatch
wlsxConfigurationLicenseMismatch.description: This trap indicates the configuration update status in the case where some configuration could not be applied due to missing licenses.

wlsxVoiceCdrBufferThresholdReached.name: wlsxVoiceCdrBufferThresholdReached
wlsxVoiceCdrBufferThresholdReached.description: This trap indicates that the CDR buffer threshold has been reached

wlsxTunnelUp.name: wlsxTunnelUp
wlsxTunnelUp.description: This trap indicates that a tunnel interface is up.

wlsxTunnelDown.name: wlsxTunnelDown
wlsxTunnelDown.description: This trap indicates that a tunnel interface is down.

wlsxMeshNodeEntryChanged.name: wlsxMeshNodeEntryChanged
wlsxMeshNodeEntryChanged.description: This trap indicates that the mesh node configuration has changed.

wlsxHtGreenfieldSupported.name: wlsxHtGreenfieldSupported
wlsxHtGreenfieldSupported.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an access point that supports HT Greenfield mode. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0005

wlsxHT40MHzIntoleranceAP.name: wlsxHT40MHzIntoleranceAP
wlsxHT40MHzIntoleranceAP.description: This trap indicates that an AP is detecting an access point with the HT 40MHz intolerance setting. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0004

wlsxHT40MHzIntoleranceSta.name: wlsxHT40MHzIntoleranceSta
wlsxHT40MHzIntoleranceSta.description: This trap indicates that the system is detecting an HT 40MHz Intolerance setting from a Station. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0004

wlsxNAuthServerAllInService.name: wlsxNAuthServerAllInService
wlsxNAuthServerAllInService.description: This trap indicates that all authentication servers is a server group are brought back in service.

wlsxNAdhocNetwork.name: wlsxNAdhocNetwork
wlsxNAdhocNetwork.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an ad hoc network where a station is connected to an ad hoc access point.

wlsxNAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedAP.name: wlsxNAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedAP
wlsxNAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedAP.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an ad hoc network that is bridging to a wired network.

wlsxNAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedSta.name: wlsxNAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedSta
wlsxNAdhocNetworkBridgeDetectedSta.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an ad hoc network that is bridging to a wired network.

wlsxNAuthMaxXsecUserEntries.name: wlsxNAuthMaxXsecUserEntries
wlsxNAuthMaxXsecUserEntries.description: A trap which indicates that the xSec user limit is reached.

wlsxNVpnMaxSessions.name: wlsxNVpnMaxSessions
wlsxNVpnMaxSessions.description: A trap which indicates that the VPN session limit is reached.

wlsxNRapExpiredPSK.name: wlsxNRapExpiredPSK
wlsxNRapExpiredPSK.description: A trap which indicates that the RAP is using the Expired PSK.

wlsxNRapWarnExpiredPSK.name: wlsxNRapWarnExpiredPSK
wlsxNRapWarnExpiredPSK.description: A trap which indicates that the Cached IKE PSK for RAPs will expire soon.

wlsxNConnectionResetWithLocal.name: wlsxNConnectionResetWithLocal
wlsxNConnectionResetWithLocal.description: A trap which indicates that tcp connection between master controller and local controller has been lost.

wlsxNApOnBackupController.name: wlsxNApOnBackupController
wlsxNApOnBackupController.description: A trap which indicates that the AP has registered with the backup controller.

wlsxClientFloodAttack.name: wlsxClientFloodAttack
wlsxClientFloodAttack.description: This trap indicates that the number of potential fake clients detected by an AP has exceeded the configured IDS threshold. This is the total number of fake clients observed across all bands. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0056

wlsxValidClientNotUsingEncryption.name: wlsxValidClientNotUsingEncryption
wlsxValidClientNotUsingEncryption.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an unencrypted data frame between a valid client and an access point.

wlsxAdhocUsingValidSSID.name: wlsxAdhocUsingValidSSID
wlsxAdhocUsingValidSSID.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an ad hoc network using a valid/protected SSID. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0008

wlsxAPSpoofingDetected.name: wlsxAPSpoofingDetected
wlsxAPSpoofingDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that one of its virtual APs is being spoofed using MAC spoofing. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019

wlsxClientAssociatingOnWrongChannel.name: wlsxClientAssociatingOnWrongChannel
wlsxClientAssociatingOnWrongChannel.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a client trying to associate to one of its BSSIDs on the wrong channel. This can be a sign that the BSSID is being spoofed in order to fool the client into thinking the AP is operating on another channel.

wlsxNDisconnectStationAttack.name: wlsxNDisconnectStationAttack
wlsxNDisconnectStationAttack.description: This trap indicates that an AP has determined that a client is under Disconnect Attack because the rate of Assoc/Reassoc Response packets received by that client exceeds the configured threshold. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0048

wlsxNStaUnAssociatedFromUnsecureAP.name: wlsxNStaUnAssociatedFromUnsecureAP
wlsxNStaUnAssociatedFromUnsecureAP.description: This trap indicates that an AP that had previously detected a client association to a Rogue access point is no longer detecting that association.

wlsxOmertaAttack.name: wlsxOmertaAttack
wlsxOmertaAttack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an Omerta attack. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0053

wlsxTKIPReplayAttack.name: wlsxTKIPReplayAttack
wlsxTKIPReplayAttack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a possible TKIP replay attack. If successful this could be the precursor to more advanced attacks. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0013

wlsxChopChopAttack.name: wlsxChopChopAttack
wlsxChopChopAttack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a ChopChop attack. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0038

wlsxFataJackAttack.name: wlsxFataJackAttack
wlsxFataJackAttack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a FATA-Jack attack. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0057

wlsxInvalidAddressCombination.name: wlsxInvalidAddressCombination
wlsxInvalidAddressCombination.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an invalid source and destination combination. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0011

wlsxValidClientMisassociation.name: wlsxValidClientMisassociation
wlsxValidClientMisassociation.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a misassociation between a valid client and an unsafe AP.

wlsxMalformedHTIEDetected.name: wlsxMalformedHTIEDetected
wlsxMalformedHTIEDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a malformed HT Information Element. This can be the result of a misbehaving wireless driver or it may be an indication of a new wireless attack.

wlsxMalformedAssocReqDetected.name: wlsxMalformedAssocReqDetected
wlsxMalformedAssocReqDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a malformed association request with a NULL SSID. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0010

wlsxOverflowIEDetected.name: wlsxOverflowIEDetected
wlsxOverflowIEDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a management frame with a malformed information element. The declared length of the element is larger than the entire frame containing the element. This may be used to corrupt or crash wireless drivers. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0008

wlsxOverflowEAPOLKeyDetected.name: wlsxOverflowEAPOLKeyDetected
wlsxOverflowEAPOLKeyDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a key in an EAPOL Key message with a specified length greater than the length of the entire message. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0009

wlsxMalformedFrameLargeDurationDetected.name: wlsxMalformedFrameLargeDurationDetected
wlsxMalformedFrameLargeDurationDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an unusually large duration in a wireless frame. This may be an attempt to block other devices from transmitting. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0051

wlsxMalformedFrameWrongChannelDetected.name: wlsxMalformedFrameWrongChannelDetected
wlsxMalformedFrameWrongChannelDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a beacon on one channel advertising another channel. This could be an attempt to lure clients away from a valid AP. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0050

wlsxMalformedAuthFrame.name: wlsxMalformedAuthFrame
wlsxMalformedAuthFrame.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an authentication frame with either a bad algorithm (similar to Fata-Jack) or a bad transaction. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0057

wlsxCTSRateAnomaly.name: wlsxCTSRateAnomaly
wlsxCTSRateAnomaly.description: This trap indicates that the rate of CTS packets received by an AP exceeds the configured IDS threshold.

wlsxRTSRateAnomaly.name: wlsxRTSRateAnomaly
wlsxRTSRateAnomaly.description: This trap indicates that the rate of RTS packets received by an AP exceeds the configured IDS threshold.

wlsxNRogueAPDetected.name: wlsxNRogueAPDetected
wlsxNRogueAPDetected.description: This trap indicates that an unauthorized access point is connected to the wired network. The access point is classified as Rogue by the system.

wlsxNRogueAPResolved.name: wlsxNRogueAPResolved
wlsxNRogueAPResolved.description: This trap indicates that a previously detected access point, classified as Rogue, is either no longer present in the network or it changed its state.

wlsxNeighborAPDetected.name: wlsxNeighborAPDetected
wlsxNeighborAPDetected.description: This trap indicates that an access point has been classified as a Neighbor by the system.

wlsxNInterferingAPDetected.name: wlsxNInterferingAPDetected
wlsxNInterferingAPDetected.description: This trap indicates that an access point has been classified as Interfering by the system. The access point is declared Interfering because it is not authorized, nor has it been classified as a Rogue.

wlsxNSuspectRogueAPDetected.name: wlsxNSuspectRogueAPDetected
wlsxNSuspectRogueAPDetected.description: This trap indicates that an access point, classified as Suspected Rogue, is detected by the system. The AP is suspected to be rogue with the supplied confidence level.

wlsxNSuspectRogueAPResolved.name: wlsxNSuspectRogueAPResolved
wlsxNSuspectRogueAPResolved.description: This trap indicates that a previously detected access point, classified as Suspected Rogue, is either no longer present in the network or has changed its state.

wlsxBlockAckAttackDetected.name: wlsxBlockAckAttackDetected
wlsxBlockAckAttackDetected.description: This trap indicates that an attempt has been made to deny service to the source address by spoofing a block ACK add request that sets a sequence number window outside the currently used window. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2008-0006

wlsxHotspotterAttackDetected.name: wlsxHotspotterAttackDetected
wlsxHotspotterAttackDetected.description: This trap indicates that a new AP has appeared immediately following a client probe request. This is indicative of the Hotspotter tool or similar that attempts to trap clients with a fake hotspot or other wireless network. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0054

wlsxNSignatureMatch.name: wlsxNSignatureMatch
wlsxNSignatureMatch.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match in a frame.

wlsxNSignatureMatchNetstumbler.name: wlsxNSignatureMatchNetstumbler
wlsxNSignatureMatchNetstumbler.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Netstumbler in a frame. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0025

wlsxNSignatureMatchAsleap.name: wlsxNSignatureMatchAsleap
wlsxNSignatureMatchAsleap.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for ASLEAP in a frame. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0027

wlsxNSignatureMatchAirjack.name: wlsxNSignatureMatchAirjack
wlsxNSignatureMatchAirjack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Airjack in a frame. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0018

wlsxNSignatureMatchNullProbeResp.name: wlsxNSignatureMatchNullProbeResp
wlsxNSignatureMatchNullProbeResp.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Null-Probe-Response in a frame. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0064

wlsxNSignatureMatchDeauthBcast.name: wlsxNSignatureMatchDeauthBcast
wlsxNSignatureMatchDeauthBcast.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Deauth-Broadcast in a frame. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0045

wlsxNSignatureMatchDisassocBcast.name: wlsxNSignatureMatchDisassocBcast
wlsxNSignatureMatchDisassocBcast.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Disassoc-Broadcast in a frame. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0019 http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0046

wlsxNSignatureMatchWellenreiter.name: wlsxNSignatureMatchWellenreiter
wlsxNSignatureMatchWellenreiter.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a signature match for Wellenreiter in a frame. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2006-0058

wlsxAPDeauthContainment.name: wlsxAPDeauthContainment
wlsxAPDeauthContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain an access point by disconnecting its client.

wlsxClientDeauthContainment.name: wlsxClientDeauthContainment
wlsxClientDeauthContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain a client by disconnecting it from the AP that it is associated with.

wlsxAPWiredContainment.name: wlsxAPWiredContainment
wlsxAPWiredContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain an access point by disrupting traffic to its client on the wired interface.

wlsxClientWiredContainment.name: wlsxClientWiredContainment
wlsxClientWiredContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain a client by disrupting traffic to it on the wired interface.

wlsxAPTaggedWiredContainment.name: wlsxAPTaggedWiredContainment
wlsxAPTaggedWiredContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain an access point by disrupting traffic to its client on the wired interface.

wlsxClientTaggedWiredContainment.name: wlsxClientTaggedWiredContainment
wlsxClientTaggedWiredContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain a client by disrupting traffic to it on the wired interface.

wlsxTarpitContainment.name: wlsxTarpitContainment
wlsxTarpitContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain an access point by moving a client that is attempting to associate to it to a tarpit.

wlsxVoiceClientLocationUpdate.name: wlsxVoiceClientLocationUpdate
wlsxVoiceClientLocationUpdate.description: This trap indicates that the location of voice client has been changed.

wlsxAPChannelChange.name: wlsxAPChannelChange
wlsxAPChannelChange.description: This trap indicates that an AP changed its channel.

wlsxAPPowerChange.name: wlsxAPPowerChange
wlsxAPPowerChange.description: This trap indicates that an AP changed its transmit power level.

wlsxAPModeChange.name: wlsxAPModeChange
wlsxAPModeChange.description: This trap indicates that an AP changed its mode from AP to APMonitor or vice versa.

wlsxUserEntryAttributesChanged.name: wlsxUserEntryAttributesChanged
wlsxUserEntryAttributesChanged.description: This trap indicates that the user entry attributes have changed.

wlsxPowerSaveDosAttack.name: wlsxPowerSaveDosAttack
wlsxPowerSaveDosAttack.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a Power Save DoS attack.

wlsxNAPMasterStatusChange.name: wlsxNAPMasterStatusChange
wlsxNAPMasterStatusChange.description: This trap indicates that the status of the AP as seen by the master controller has changed.

wlsxNAdhocUsingValidSSID.name: wlsxNAdhocUsingValidSSID
wlsxNAdhocUsingValidSSID.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected an ad hoc network node using a valid/protected SSID. For more info check: http://www.wve.org/entries/show/WVE-2005-0008

wlsxCRLExpired.name: wlsxCRLExpired
wlsxCRLExpired.description: This trap indicates that the CRL associated with the particular Trustpoint is expired.

wlsxMgmtUserAuthenticationFailed.name: wlsxMgmtUserAuthenticationFailed
wlsxMgmtUserAuthenticationFailed.description: This trap indicates that a management user authentication has failed.

wlsxNConnectionBackfromLocal.name: wlsxNConnectionBackfromLocal
wlsxNConnectionBackfromLocal.description: A trap which indicates that tcp connection between master controller and local controller is back.

wlsxAPNumUpgradeFailure.name: wlsxAPNumUpgradeFailure
wlsxAPNumUpgradeFailure.description: A trap which indicates the number of upgrade failure of an access point.

wlsxAPNumWarmStarts.name: wlsxAPNumWarmStarts
wlsxAPNumWarmStarts.description: A trap which indicates the number of warm starts of an access point.

wlsxAPNumColdStarts.name: wlsxAPNumColdStarts
wlsxAPNumColdStarts.description: A trap which indicates the number of cold starts of an access point.

wlsxAPNumDown.name: wlsxAPNumDown
wlsxAPNumDown.description: A trap which indicates the number of down alarms of an access point.

wlsxAPNumRadioDown.name: wlsxAPNumRadioDown
wlsxAPNumRadioDown.description: A trap which indicates the number of radio down alarms of an access point.

wlsxNumClockSyncErrors.name: wlsxNumClockSyncErrors
wlsxNumClockSyncErrors.description: A trap which indicates the total number of clock sync errors between the switch and access points.

wlsxNumColdStart.name: wlsxNumColdStart
wlsxNumColdStart.description: A trap which indicates the number of cold-starts of the switch.

wlsxNumWarmStart.name: wlsxNumWarmStart
wlsxNumWarmStart.description: A trap which indicates the number of warm-starts of the switch.

wlsxWirelessHostedNetworkDetected.name: wlsxWirelessHostedNetworkDetected
wlsxWirelessHostedNetworkDetected.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected a wireless client that is hosting a softAP. The softAP could be used to share the hosting client's wired or wireless network connection with other wireless users.

wlsxClientAssociatedToHostedNetwork.name: wlsxClientAssociatedToHostedNetwork
wlsxClientAssociatedToHostedNetwork.description: This trap indicates that an AP detected that a wireless client associated to an access point that is hosted by another wireless client.

wlsxThresholdExceeded.name: wlsxThresholdExceeded
wlsxThresholdExceeded.description: A trap indicates a particular resource under monitoring has gone above the threshold specified.

wlsxThresholdCleared.name: wlsxThresholdCleared
wlsxThresholdCleared.description: A trap indicates a particular resource under monitoring has come below the threshold specified.

wlsxWirelessHostedNetworkContainment.name: wlsxWirelessHostedNetworkContainment
wlsxWirelessHostedNetworkContainment.description: This trap indicates that containment is being enforced on a client associated to a hosted network.

wlsxHostOfWirelessNetworkContainment.name: wlsxHostOfWirelessNetworkContainment
wlsxHostOfWirelessNetworkContainment.description: This trap indicates that containment is being enforced on a client that is hosting a wireless hosted network.

wlsxEnhancedAdhocContainment.name: wlsxEnhancedAdhocContainment
wlsxEnhancedAdhocContainment.description: This trap indicates that an AP has attempted to contain an adhoc node by disconnecting it from other members of the adhoc network.

wlsxPowerSupplyOKTrap.name: wlsxPowerSupplyOKTrap
wlsxPowerSupplyOKTrap.description: This trap indicates that the system power supply condition have returned to normal operation status.

wlsxPowerSupplyFailureTrap.name: wlsxPowerSupplyFailureTrap
wlsxPowerSupplyFailureTrap.description: A trap which indicates that the power supply has failed.

wlsxFanTrayRemovedTrap.name: wlsxFanTrayRemovedTrap
wlsxFanTrayRemovedTrap.description: A Trap which indicates that a fan tray is removed.

wlsxFanTrayInsertedTrap.name: wlsxFanTrayInsertedTrap
wlsxFanTrayInsertedTrap.description: A Trap which indicates that a fan tray is inserted.

wlsxPowerSupplyMissingTrap.name: wlsxPowerSupplyMissingTrap
wlsxPowerSupplyMissingTrap.description: A Trap which indicates that the power supply is missing.

wlsxStackTopologyChangeTrap.name: wlsxStackTopologyChangeTrap
wlsxStackTopologyChangeTrap.description: When change happens in any topology of the stack element in the stack, then a notification is sent to the Management Entity.

wlsxStackIfStateChangeTrap.name: wlsxStackIfStateChangeTrap
wlsxStackIfStateChangeTrap.description: When any stacking interface in any stack element joins or leaves stacking topology, then a notification is sent to the Management Entity with slot and interface information.

wlsxLicenseServerExpiry.name: wlsxLicenseServerExpiry
wlsxLicenseServerExpiry.description: A Trap which indicates that licenses sent from the license server will expire in wlsxTrapLicenseServerDaysRemaining days.

wlsxLicenseClientExpiry.name: wlsxLicenseClientExpiry
wlsxLicenseClientExpiry.description: A Trap which indicates that licenses contributed by a license client will expire in wlsxTrapLicenseClientDaysRemaining days.

wlsxIfStateChangeTrap.name: wlsxIfStateChangeTrap
wlsxIfStateChangeTrap.description: When the link state of an interface changes due to reason specified by wlsxIfStateChangeReason object, a notification is sent to the Management Entity with reason for this state change and interface information.

wlsxWMSOffloadRecommended.name: wlsxWMSOffloadRecommended
wlsxWMSOffloadRecommended.description: This trap indicates that current state in the WMS module shows that WMS is reaching capacity, and so it is recommended to enable WMS-Offload.

wlsxAPActiveUplinkChanged.name: wlsxAPActiveUplinkChanged
wlsxAPActiveUplinkChanged.description: When the active uplink of an AP changes, a notification is sent to the Management Entity with the new uplink type

wlsxCertExpiringSoon.name: wlsxCertExpiringSoon
wlsxCertExpiringSoon.description: This trap indicates that a particular Certificate is going to expire in less than 60 days.

wlsxCertExpired.name: wlsxCertExpired
wlsxCertExpired.description: This trap indicates that a particular Certificate has expired and is no longer valid.

wlsxAPManagedModeConfigFailureTrap.name: wlsxAPManagedModeConfigFailureTrap
wlsxAPManagedModeConfigFailureTrap.description: This trap indicates that config apply has failed on the IAP.
